        <td>
          <para styleclass="Body Table"><image src="Red-14-1.gif" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption" figurelistinclude="0"></image><text styleclass="Parameter-Header"> Radial Clearance (</text><text styleclass="Parameter">mm</text><text styleclass="Parameter-Header">) </text><text styleclass="Body Text"> Default = 0 </text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><table styleclass="Block" rowcount="3" colcount="1">
            <tr style="vertical-align:top">
              <td>
                <para styleclass="Normal"><image src="MD-DIALOG-2DCAM-COORDINATES-RADIAL-CLEARANCE.ipp" scale="-99.90%" styleclass="Image Caption" figurelistinclude="0"><caption><![CDATA[Cam without Radial Clearance]]></caption></image></para>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr style="vertical-align:top">
              <td>
                <para styleclass="Normal"><image src="MD-DIALOG-2DCAM-COORDINATES-RADIAL-CLEARANCE-1.ipp" scale="-99.90%" styleclass="Image Caption" figurelistinclude="0"><caption><![CDATA[Cam with 0.2mm Radial Clearance]]></caption></image></para>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr style="vertical-align:top">
              <td>
                <para styleclass="Body Table"><text styleclass="Notes">Note</text><text styleclass="Body Text">: </text></para>
                <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">This parameter<text styleclass="Body Text"> will offset the true Cam-Profile to calculate a new Cam-Profile.</text></para>
                <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#993300;" /></para>
                <para styleclass="Body Table"><text styleclass="VariableName">E.G.1: Groove-Cam</text> (<text styleclass="Body Text HowTo">+) : you may need to add a </text>small<text styleclass="Body Text HowTo"> clearance to make sure the Cam-Follower bearing can slide/roll along the two Cam-Flanks in the Groove. </text></para>
                <para styleclass="Body Table"><text styleclass="VariableName">E.G. 2: Conjugate-Cam</text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo"> (+) : you may decide to add a small clearance to compensate for tolerances in the cam assembly. </text></para>
                <para styleclass="Body Table"><text styleclass="VariableName">E.G. 3: Rough-Cut</text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo"> (–) : you may want to export data for a rough-cut of the cam.</text></para>
                <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#993300;" /></para>
                <para styleclass="VariableName">Notes: </para>
                <list id="0" type="ol" listtype="lower-alpha" formatstring="&#37;&#48;&#58;&#115;&#41;" format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="Body Text HowTo" style="font-family:&apos;Noto Sans&apos;; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;">
                  <li styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text styleclass="Body Text">This parameter is copied and repeated in the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Dialog-FunctionBlock-CamCoordinates" styleclass="SeeAlso">Cam-Coordinates dialog-box</link><text styleclass="Body Text">.</text></li>
                  <li styleclass="Body Text HowTo">Stud-type Cam-Followers often have a large negative tolerance - e.g. <equation styleclass="Body Text;vertical-align:text-bottom" style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; font-style:normal; text-decoration:none; text-transform:none; vertical-align:baseline; color:#000000; background-color:transparent; letter-spacing:normal; letter-scaling:100%;" font-size="26"><![CDATA[0\  - \ 50\mu m]]></equation><text styleclass="Body Text"> - which may give enough clearance, or too much clearance, for a Groove-Cam!</text></li>
                </list>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </table></para>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#993300;" /></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="width:228px;">
          <para styleclass="Normal" style="text-align:right;"><image src="MD-RADIUSCURVATUREWARNING.ipp" scale="-99.90%" styleclass="Image Caption" figurelistinclude="0"><caption><![CDATA[Cam-Profile RED = Warning]]></caption></image></para>
        </td>
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Body Table"><image src="Red-14-2.gif" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption" figurelistinclude="0"></image><text styleclass="Parameter-Header"> Cam ROC &apos;Soft-Limit&apos; ( %)</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Table"><text styleclass="Body Text">Default - see </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Dialog-Application-Settings" anchor="App-General" styleclass="SeeAlso">Application Settings</link><text styleclass="SeeAlso"> &gt; General tab &gt; Cam Radius Soft-Limits = Default value.</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text">This parameter applies as a warning for the <text styleclass="Element">2D-cam</text> you are editing, only.</para>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#993300;" /></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><table styleclass="Block" rowcount="1" colcount="1">
            <tr style="vertical-align:top">
              <td>
                <para styleclass="Body Table"><text styleclass="VariableName" style="color:#ff0000;">Warning if: </text><text styleclass="Body Text">&#32;</text><equation styleclass="Body Text;vertical-align:middle" style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; font-style:normal; text-decoration:none; text-transform:none; vertical-align:baseline; color:#000000; background-color:transparent; letter-spacing:normal; letter-scaling:100%;vertical-align:text-bottom" font-size="28" color="#0039e3"><![CDATA[ \left| \lfrac{Roc_{cam}}{R_{foll}} \right|\times 100\percent < \left( Soft-Limit \right)\percent]]></equation></para>
                <para styleclass="VariableName">If ABSOLUTE of <text styleclass="Interface2">Cam&apos;s Radius-of-Curvature</text><text styleclass="Interface2" style="font-size:14pt;"> &lt;</text>&#32;<text styleclass="Parameter-Header">Cam Radius &apos;Soft-Limit&apos;</text>&#32;<text styleclass="Interface2">× Roller Radius</text>&#32;</para>
                <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text styleclass="Body Text">As a </text><text styleclass="VariableName" style="color:#ff0000;">warning</text><text styleclass="Body Text"> only, </text>the <text styleclass="VariableName">Cam-Profile</text> is <text styleclass="Interface2" style="color:#ff0000;">RED</text><text styleclass="Element" style="color:#ff0000;">.</text></para>
                <para styleclass="Body Text">You should inspect your Cam for undercutting, high contact-stress, low life, ...</para>
                <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#993300;" /></para>
                <para styleclass="Body Text">E.g. : If <text styleclass="Parameter-Header">Cam ROC &apos;Soft-Limit&apos; = 100%</text> : </para>
                <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">The <text styleclass="VariableName">Cam-Profile</text> is <text styleclass="Interface2" style="color:#ff0000;">RED</text> where the <text styleclass="VariableName">Cam&apos;s Radius-of-Curvature</text> is less than the <text styleclass="VariableName">Roller&apos;s Radius. </text></para>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </table></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
